A Magistrates’ Court in Abeokuta on Friday, sentenced a 23-year-old ex-convict, Adesanya Segun, to seven years imprisonment for stealing recharge cards worth N6,000. Magistrate Olakunleyin Oke sentenced Segun following a guilty plea to theft. ”The convict is not ready to change from his stealing habits. You are sentenced to seven years with an option of fine,” the magistrate held. ALSO READ: Ojude oba festival:  Model of religious tolerance Court remands pastor, two others in prison over alleged… Two dragged to court over conspiracy, false information in… Three men arraigned over alleged possession of human skulls Ile Arugbo: Court fixes hearing of motion on notice for… Earlier, the Prosecution Counsel, Insp. Olu-Balogun Lawrence told the court that the convict committed the offence on Dec.22,2019 at about 9.30 a.m at Malomo Junction Oke Aregba of Abeokuta. Lawrence said that the convict entered into the shop of the complainant, Mrs Adeosun Olaide, and stole N15,000 cash and recharge cards. He said Segun had served one-year imprisonment for theft. The prosecutor said that the offence contravened the provisions of Section 390(9) of the Criminal Code Vol.1 Law of Ogun, 2006. (NAN) STAY STRONGER, LONGER AND SATISFY MADAM LIKE NEVER BEFORE WITH THIS NATURAL SUPPLEMENTS WITH NO SIDE EFFECTS. CLICK NOW. CLICK HERE NOW TO  WORK FROM HOME ENTIRELY AT YOUR OWN CONVINIENCE AND GET PAID WEEKLY, DIRECTLY INTO YOUR BANK ACCOUNT.REGISTRATION IS FREE PREMATURE EJACULATION, SMALL SIZE FINALLY CURED NATURALLY IN 2 WEEKS FOR BIGGER, LONGER, HARDER SEXIER SEX WITH NEW MAN MACHINE